Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g}(lengthways) into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips
(no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{2%tbsp}, season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.
> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

In the meantime, halve, peel, and slice the @red onion{1/2}(peeled and sliced thinly).

Pop it into a medium #bowl{} and add the @red wine vinegar{12%ml} and @sugar{1/2%tsp}
for the pickle. Add a pinch of @salt{pinch}, mix together and set aside.

Meanwhile, cut the @medium tomato{1}(cut into 1cm chunks). Add to the bowl
of pickled onions and stir through the @olive oil{1%tbsp}(for dressing). Toss
to coat in the dressing.

Put a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough oil to completely coat
the bottom of the pan.

Once hot, carefully add the @ready to eat falafels{171%g} to the pan and reduce
the heat to medium-high. Cook until golden, ~{2-4%minutes}. Adjust the heat
as necessary.

Once cooked, remove from the heat and drizzle over the @honey{15%g}. Turn the
falafels in the honey to coat.
> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

When everything's nearly ready, add @butter{30%g}, @red pepper chilli jelly{25%g}
and @smoked paprika{1%sachet} to a small #saucepan{} on medium heat. Warm to
melt the butter, ~{1%minute}. Stir the sauce well to combine.

Just before you're ready to serve, toss the @baby leaf mix{20%g} with the pickled
onion and tomato.
> TIP: Don't add the leaves too early or they'll go soggy.

Spoon a dollop of @houmous{100%g} onto each of your #serving plates{}.

Place your falafels on top and drizzle over the paprika butter.

Serve with your chips and salad alongside.

Enjoy!